Program link:
https://www.hackerrank.com/contests/rookierank/challenges/birthday-cake-candles
Program:
Colleen is having a birthday! She will have a cake with one candle for each year of her age. When she blows out the candles, sheâ€™ll only be able to blow out the tallest ones.

Find and print the number of candles she can successfully blow out.

Input Format

The first line contains a single integer, , denoting the number of candles on the cake. 
The second line contains  space-separated integers, where each integer  describes the height of candle .

Constraints

Output Format 
Print the number of candles the can be blown out on a new line.

Sample Input 0

4
3 2 1 3
Sample Output 0

2
Explanation 0

The maximum candle height is 3 and there are two candles of that height.
Code:
import java.io.*;
import java.math.*;
import java.text.*;
import java.util.*;
import java.util.regex.*;

public class Solution {

    /*
     * Complete the birthdayCakeCandles function below.
     */
    static int getMax(int arr[]){
        int max=0;
        for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
            if(arr[i]>max){
                max=arr[i];
            }
        }
        return max;
    }
    static int birthdayCakeCandles(int n, int[] ar) {
        /*
         * Write your code here.
         */
        int count=0;
        int x=getMax(ar);
        for(int i=0;i<ar.length;i++){
            if(ar[i]==x){
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;

    }

    private static final Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);

    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        BufferedWriter bw = new BufferedWriter(new FileWriter(System.getenv("OUTPUT_PATH")));

        int n = Integer.parseInt(scan.nextLine().trim());

        int[] ar = new int[n];

        String[] arItems = scan.nextLine().split(" ");

        for (int arItr = 0; arItr < n; arItr++) {
            int arItem = Integer.parseInt(arItems[arItr].trim());
            ar[arItr] = arItem;
        }

        int result = birthdayCakeCandles(n, ar);

        bw.write(String.valueOf(result));
        bw.newLine();

        bw.close();
    }
}
